<td box="[1001,1404,1639,1733]" gridcol="2" gridrow="8" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Northern extreme of Central Cordillera of Colombia (Amalfi, Antioquia department, Colombia)</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1781,2059]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1451,158,292]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">
The new Serra do Cachimbo species also differs from its Amazonian Brazilian congeners by the nodal line bearing a horizontal corky flange ca. 
<quantity box="[550,614,1817,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long (vs. a downward shield-like corky flange in 
<taxonomicName authority="McClure" authorityName="McClure" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis box="[1166,1452,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Arthrostylidium scandens</emphasis>
McClure
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Maguire, B. &amp; Wurdack, J. J." box="[271,595,1853,1879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" pagination="1 - 278" refId="ref25579" refString="Maguire, B. &amp; Wurdack, J. J. (1964) The Botany of the Guayana Highland - Part V. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 10 (5): 1 - 278." type="journal article" year="1964">Maguire &amp; Wurdack 1964: 4</bibRefCitation>
); nodal fimbriae absent (vs. a uniform band of abundant whitish-yellow cilia up to 
<quantity box="[200,266,1889,1916]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long in 
<taxonomicName authority="Judziewicz &amp; Clark 1993: 84" authorityName="Judziewicz &amp; Clark" authorityPageNumber="84" authorityYear="1993" box="[358,875,1889,1915]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fimbrinodum">
<emphasis box="[358,535,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">A. fimbrinodum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[542,875,1889,1915]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" pagination="80 - 99" refId="ref24854" refString="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G. (1993) The South American Species of Arthrostylidium (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae). Systematic Botany 18 (1): 80 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2419790" type="journal article" year="1993">Judziewicz &amp; Clark 1993: 84</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); culm leaf blades 
<quantity box="[1086,1219,1889,1916]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.26" metricValueMax="2.42" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="cm" value="22.6" valueMax="24.2" valueMin="21.0">21–24.2 cm</quantity>
long, lanceolate and apex acuminate (vs. 
<quantity box="[373,501,1925,1952]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="cm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.8 cm</quantity>
long, triangular lanceolate and apex setose in 
<taxonomicName box="[1038,1254,1925,1951]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simpliciusculum">
<emphasis box="[1038,1254,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">A. simpliciusculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and foliage leaf sheath extension absent, inner ligule ca. 
<quantity box="[596,662,1961,1988]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, auricle symmetrical and fimbriate (vs. sheath extension up to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long on one side, inner ligule elongate on opposite side of the sheath extension, 
<quantity box="[1103,1211,1997,2024]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10 mm</quantity>
long and auricle and fimbriae absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Judziewicz &amp; Clark 1993: 88" authorityName="Judziewicz &amp; Clark" authorityPageNumber="88" authorityYear="1993" box="[347,866,2033,2059]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandifolium">
<emphasis box="[347,525,2033,2059]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">A. grandifolium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[532,866,2033,2059]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" pagination="80 - 99" refId="ref24854" refString="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G. (1993) The South American Species of Arthrostylidium (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae). Systematic Botany 18 (1): 80 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2419790" type="journal article" year="1993">Judziewicz &amp; Clark 1993: 88</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). The latter has, along with 
<taxonomicName box="[1181,1372,2033,2059]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboense">
<emphasis box="[1181,1372,2033,2059]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">A. cachimboense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Londono &amp; Clark (1998: 412)" authorityName="Londono &amp; Clark" authorityPageNumber="412" authorityYear="1998" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="107" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiribiquetensis">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">A. chiribiquetensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[325,674,158,184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" pagination="408 - 428" refId="ref25340" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (1998) Eight new taxa and two new reports of Bambuseae (Poaceae: Bambusoideae) from Colombia. Novon 8: 408 - 428. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391866" type="journal article" year="1998">Londoño &amp; Clark (1998: 412)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(known from the Serranía de Chiribiquete, department of 
<collectingRegion box="[1353,1448,158,184]" country="Colombia" name="Caqueta" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Caquetá</collectingRegion>
, Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[291,406,194,221]" name="Colombia" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Colombia</collectingCountry>
), the largest foliage leaf blades known for the genus so far, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono &amp; Clark" authorityYear="1998" box="[1153,1366,194,221]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthrostylidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chiribiquetensis">
<emphasis box="[1153,1366,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">A. chiribiquetensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the pithy, canaliculate culms, the basally inflated culm leaf blades and foliage leaf blades tessellate, bearing reddish fimbriae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
